                    <div id="page-content">
                        

<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong>« <a href="/news-04-2018">April 2018</a> | <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="/news-05-2018">May 2018</a></span> | <a href="/news-06-2018">June 2018</a> »</strong></p>
</div>
<div style="border: 2px solid black; background-color: Moccasin;">
<p style="text-align: center;">The dynamic nature of this wiki means that linked pages might get moved, renamed, deleted, or replaced. Old news pages remain as time capsules and are not updated to account for these changes.</p>
</div>
<p>Welcome to this installment of site news, where something, something May the Fourth meme!</p>
<p>This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup>, and fan-content for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</p>
<h4 id="toc0"><span>Featured Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>The featured articles for May were <a href="/scp-2881">SCP-2881</a> &quot;The Tree You Cannot Climb&quot; by Zmax15, <a href="/astronomical">Astronomical</a> by Sophia Light, and P'rantortiz the Vile by Shaggydredlocks! The first is about an escalating threat is put to the test, the second a chilling account of a dying world, and the third is a Black Queen-article about an ancient evil! Check 'em out!</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc1"><span>Event Featured Articles</span></h4>
<p>The theme for the month of May was <em>wooden</em>!</p>
<ul>
<li>In <a href="/scp-805">SCP-805</a> (Poison Wood Foal) by Aura Vesta a coarse colt carries a calcifying contagion!</li>
<li>In <a href="/scp-3197">SCP-3197</a> (A Trickster God for the Modern Age) by ZoltanBerrigomo, one can be led to wealth and prosperity through the power of prayer and Alan Greenspan!</li>
<li>In <a href="/scp-421">SCP-421</a> (Shoal of Driftwood) by Sirava a mass of hungry, hungry detritus stalks the briny deep!</li>
</ul>
